Hey, guess what? I couldn't decide what I wanted for Christmas. So, I decided I would ask for something I actually need. (That's a first... :D) I decided to ask for a laptop. I know that I already have one for school, but it gets taken away next year, and I will really need it for next year. 

    That's why I'm only asking for one thing, but it's something that I really need. 

All of the Christmas decorations that my family owns are put up. We already have one Christmas tree set up, but we're getting another one this weekend. Crazy!!!!!!! 


ttyl...
http://principessa1392.livejournal.com/6118.html

Hooray! Today is Wednesday. It's not a Friday, I kn ow, but it's closer to friday than Monday is! Te He He! 

Another good thing about this Wednesday is that we get off school early. But the bad thing about this particular wednesday is that it's picture day. If you read what I sadi before about the retake day, just forget about it. Because this time, I don't care what my picture looks like. I mean, it's not the last picture I'll ever take, right? 

Well, anyway. Lets be happy again! It's a wednesday! 

I get off school early...I get off school early...I get off school early...I get off school early...I get off school early...I get off school early...I get off school early...I get off school early...I get off school early...I get off school early...I get off school early...

ttyl

So, tomorrow, we have picture retakes. My original picture was soooooooo bad. I totally forgot about Picture Day, so I was wearing a sweatshirt. Ugh! It was soooooo bad. But, I will be getting retakes! Thank God!!!

Knowing me, I won't get a good retake either. Oh well. It's just a picture, right? WRONG!!! A picture of you is supposed to reflect who you are, and your personallity. Well, I guess that my personallity will have to be pretty looking tomorrow, or Im screwed... :o!!!

Oh well. And, I wont know what happens until we get the pics back. 

Wish me luck...


1-2-3 CHEESE!!!


Smile pretty...
http://principessa1392.livejournal.com/5470.html

Thanksgiving Vacation was pretty cool. You know, the usual stuff. All the weird relatives that you haven't seen in years come down, and sleep in your room, and you get stuck on the livingroom floor with your little sister. Fun!

But then, after the really great part (the above)then I went up to my grandparents to see all my cousin. I have five on my dad's side of the family, and we're all pretty close. My cousins and I are all within 8 months of eachother. We're all girls! 

At least we got snow and had no school. That part was pretty cool. Well, we got snow! THat was awesome. I love snow. Snow snow, I love snow! I'm absolutely, positively wild about snow! Can't go around it, gotta go through it! Beautiful, loveable, super-duper snow! I like snow... :D

Another cool part about the break was Harry Potter 4. It was really good except for the fact that they didn't even film the quidditch world cup!!! I got over it after the 3rd time of watching the movie, though!

Oh well. I guess over all, that I had a pretty good Thanksgiving Vacation. How about you?

OMG! Thank GOD It's friday!!!1


I am soooooooo happy. My cousin who is 7 months old is coming on Saturday!!! She is THE cutest baby in the world! (besides Sarah (Emily :D) even though I've never seen her... :D) Oh, this Thanksgiving Break will be awesome!!!!  My entire family is coming up sometime this week, and my house will be jam packed with people! 

I am sooo unbeleiveably happy that we have no school for an entire week! YES YEs YES!!! I am sooo excited!!!

I also love thanksgiving! I especialy like pumpkin bread. My aunt Diane lives in connecticut, and whenever she and my uncle and cuzins cum up 2 maine, they bring Pumpkin bread for me! <3  So nice!!!

OMG! I am soooooo nervous. You would not believe. Okay, so maybe you would. But this is my first level 2 assesment this year. It's in science, and it's on minerals. BOOORING!!!!!  That's what made it so hard to study. I hate minerals, yet i've had to study them EVERY night for the past 3 weeks. 

I am soooo nervous. I think im gonna fail it. Then, I'll have an even lower grade than i have now! I meen, a B isn't THAT bad, right? Cuz thats wat i have. 

I have the test next period and I don't think that I'm ready for it. I'm supposed to be reaading right now, so I can't very well study. O well. I'll just have to go by what little I now on the classification of minerals and ATTEMPT (key word: attempt) to get higher than a 2.5. 


Well, wish me luck...


~*~

So, guess what? I've just found out what this whole "mix it up day" is all about. During lunch, we have to sit with people that we don't ever sit with. The principle says that it will help to break down the social walls in our school, that prevent evryone from being "bestes buddies". 

You no, it's a nice thought, but... NO THANKS! 

Lemme tell you one thing: I really don't think any one is gonna "mix it up" with the seating arrangements we have in the cafeteria today. Ya, thanks, but no thatnks, Mrs. Brandt!


Oh, why do we have do do this stupid thing at lunch!?!?!?


GRRRR!!!!

Get a new planning committe! The entire school DOESN'T love eachother!!!!!!!

UGGHHH!!!!!

GRRRRR!

Hey! Good Morning! Well, I hate tuesdays, but at least it's not monday. What a drag! Ugh, mondays!!!!!


Guess what?!?!? Good news!!! No school on friday!!! Almost to the end of this evil week, (even though it's only Tuesday) Hey, I'm thinking posotively, okay?????


:D Ohh, I'm sonly in 2nd period. Why can't it be 7th?!?!? Tha'd b gr8. 

Right now in L.A., We're supposed to be writing. And thats what I'm doing. He didn't say what kind of writing we had to do, he just said we had to right. So i'm not doing any thing wrong, Right? Why would I care if I got in trouble anyway?!?! he he he... 

Today, because of the rain from Hurricane Wilma, there is a 75% chance that the power will go out in my school. Do you know how cool that would be? We would have to go home. No homework in like 5 subjects. That pretty much takes away all my homework. 

Well, ttyl.
:D

Hi, I'm back. Its still around the same time. OMG, I HATE school. You wanna no wat my favorite quote ever is? Well here it is anyway:


"School is practice for the future, and practice make perfect. But if nobody's perfect, why practice?"
                                                                -Billie Joe Armstrong

That is the most meaningful quote in the entire world!!!!! Even though I hate school, I still practice anyway because I wanna be a vet. That's neva gonna happen if I don't practice!

You no, it makes me feel good when I get good grades, but to do that, you have to do homework. I mean, what's the deal with that, anyway?!?!?!? I mean, c'mon! I get like an hour of homework from each teacher every night. I hate HW & SCHOOL!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!


...

Okay, I'm done ranting. :) I feel better now, thanx!
